IRWIN A. WILLIAMS v. HENRY B. SHUTE.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Russell, <T.

Decided December 30, 1880. Appeal by the sheriff of the city and county of New York from an order directing him to admit the defendant to the iail liberties. Knox & McLean, for the sheriff; Man & Parsons, for defendant.

No opinion.

Order affirmed, without costs.
